      "id": "quote",
      "type": "story",
      "title": "In the Shadow of the New Moon",
      "text": "“...so from the wells of night to the gulfs of space, and from the gulfs of space to the wells of night... Ever Their praises, and abundance to the Black Goat of the Woods.  Iä!  Shub-Niggurath!  The Goat with a Thousand Young!” \n<right><i> - H. P. Lovecraft, <i>The Whisperer in Darkness.</i>.</right>"
    },
    {
      "id": "intro",
      "text": "<i>Circus Ex Mortis</i> is an eight-part campaign for <i>Arkham Horror: The Card Game</i> for 1 -- 4 players.  This campaign is based on various works by H. P. Lovecraft and draws from real-life events, historical and mythological figures, secret societies, and of course the circus.\nAs a general notice to people who have a fear or aversion to clowns, clowns do appear in this campaign, but the art chosen for these cards avoids the typical killer clown image."
    },
